{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsRRtt3CLRoSsXNS98DM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deployed a 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster in the `elasticsearch` namespace using only native resources:\n\n- **ConfigMap `es-config`** — `elasticsearch.yml` with security enabled, HTTP/transport TLS using the existing `es-http-tls` secret (transport uses `verification_mode: certificate` since the cert's SANs only cover service-level wildcards, not per-pod hostnames).\n- **Services** — headless `es-transport` (port 9300, discovery/DNS for the StatefulSet) and `es-http` (ClusterIP, port 9200/HTTPS).\n- **StatefulSet `es`** (3 replicas, pods `es-0/1/2`) — image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`, `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` sourced from the `elastic-password` secret, TLS certs mounted from `es-http-tls`, 5Gi PVC per pod, an init container to fix data-dir ownership, and a readiness probe hitting `/_cluster/health` over HTTPS.\n- **PDB `es-pdb`** — `minAvailable: 2`.\n\nVerified: all 3 pods Ready with 0 restarts, `_cluster/health` is `green` with 3 data nodes, and a write/read/search/delete round-trip against `https://es-http:9200` succeeded with primary and replica shards distributed across nodes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":122,"cache_read_input_tokens":60619,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":122},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9d35971-1f0c-45a5-8c64-35f97b626f6c","uuid":"83837744-5ba8-4453-8c03-5a31666787c5","request_id":"req_011CcsRRsrHJtfjXPDHwyc4Y"}
